Summary: This chunk lists the methods for managing project settings, such as getting, setting, saving, and checking for changes, and includes the signal emitted when a setting is modified.

Methods:
* add_property_info(hint: Dictionary) -> void
* check_changed_settings_in_group(setting_prefix: String) -> bool
* clear(name: String) -> void
* get_changed_settings() -> PackedStringArray
* get_global_class_list() -> Array[Dictionary]
* get_order(name: String) -> int
* get_setting(name: String, default_value: Variant = null) -> Variant
* get_setting_with_override(name: StringName) -> Variant
* get_setting_with_override_and_custom_features(name: StringName, features: PackedStringArray) -> Variant
* globalize_path(path: String) -> String
* has_setting(name: String) -> bool
* load_resource_pack(pack: String, replace_files: bool = true, offset: int = 0) -> bool
* localize_path(path: String) -> String
* save() -> Error
* save_custom(file: String) -> Error
* set_as_basic(name: String, basic: bool) -> void
* set_as_internal(name: String, internal: bool) -> void
* set_initial_value(name: String, value: Variant) -> void
* set_order(name: String, position: int) -> void
* set_restart_if_changed(name: String, restart: bool) -> void
* set_setting(name: String, value: Variant) -> void

Signals:
* settings_changed(): Emitted when any setting is changed, up to once per process frame.
